---
// AI Consulting Landing Page
// Replace placeholder links with your actual Stripe Payment Links and Calendly URL

const STRIPE_INTRO_CALL_LINK = "https://buy.stripe.com/REPLACE_INTRO_CALL";
const STRIPE_RETAINER_LINK = "https://buy.stripe.com/REPLACE_RETAINER";
const CALENDLY_LINK = "https://calendly.com/REPLACE_YOUR_HANDLE";

import Layout from "../layouts/Page.astro";

const title = "AI Cost Optimization & Architecture Consulting";
const description =
  "Stop burning budget on AI infrastructure. I audit your stack, find the waste, and get paid when you save. Trusted by teams spending $100K+/mo on AI.";
---

<Layout frontmatter={{ title, subTitle: description }}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="consulting-hero full-section">
    <div class="consulting-container">
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <span class="hero-badge-dot"></span>
        Now accepting new clients
      </div>
      <h1>
        Your AI spend is<br />
        <span class="gradient-text">leaking money.</span><br />
        I find it. You keep it.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        I audit AI infrastructure for companies spending $50K+/month and
        get paid a share of what I save you — so my incentives are perfectly
        aligned with yours. No savings, no fee.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="#pricing" class="btn btn-primary btn-xl">
          See How It Works →
        </a>
        <a href={STRIPE_INTRO_CALL_LINK} class="btn btn-ghost btn-xl" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          Book 30-Min Call — $500
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-stats">
        <div class="hero-stat">
          <div class="stat-number"><span>40</span>–70%</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Typical token cost reduction</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-stat">
          <div class="stat-number">$<span>50K</span>+</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Min. monthly AI spend to qualify</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-stat">
          <div class="stat-number"><span>0</span></div>
          <div class="stat-label">Upfront risk — paid on results</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Problem -->
  <section class="consulting-problem full-section">
    <div class="consulting-container">
      <h2>AI costs compound fast.<br />Most teams don't notice until it hurts.</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">
        The teams I work with aren't doing anything wrong — they're just missing
        patterns that are nearly invisible from inside the codebase.
      </p>
      <div class="problem-grid">
        <div class="problem-item">
          <div class="problem-icon">🔁</div>
          <h3>Redundant context on every call</h3>
          <p>Sending the same system prompt, docs, or user history on every request when caching or compression would cost 90% less.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <div class="problem-icon">🧠</div>
          <h3>Wrong model for the job</h3>
          <p>GPT-4o or Claude Opus handling tasks that a fine-tuned small model or Claude Haiku would nail at 1/20th the price.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <div class="problem-icon">📦</div>
          <h3>No batching or async pipeline</h3>
          <p>Synchronous, single-shot calls where async batching would cut latency and cut costs simultaneously.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <div class="problem-icon">🏗️</div>
          <h3>Architecture that didn't scale</h3>
          <p>What worked at 1K calls/day breaks at 1M. Retrieval, embedding, and routing layers that made sense early become cost sinkholes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <div class="problem-icon">📊</div>
          <h3>No token observability</h3>
          <p>You know your invoice total but not which endpoints, features, or users are driving 80% of your spend.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <div class="problem-icon">🔐</div>
          <h3>Security gaps in the AI layer</h3>
          <p>Prompt injection surface, unconstrained agent loops, and data leakage vectors that most security audits miss entirely.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Services -->
  <section id="services" class="consulting-section full-section">
    <div class="consulting-container">
      <h2>What I do</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">
        End-to-end AI consulting from strategy to implementation — wherever
        your team needs the most leverage.
      </p>
      <div class="services-grid">
        <div class="service-card">
          <div class="service-icon">🔍</div>
          <h3>Cost &amp; Efficiency Audit</h3>
          <p>Deep analysis of your token usage, model selection, prompt architecture, caching gaps, and vendor contracts. Delivered as a ranked savings roadmap.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <div class="service-icon">🏛️</div>
          <h3>AI Architecture Review</h3>
          <p>Evaluate your retrieval pipelines, agent designs, context management, and scalability patterns. Identify what breaks at 10x current load.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <div class="service-icon">⚡</div>
          <h3>Performance Optimization</h3>
          <p>Latency reduction, throughput improvements, prompt compression, model routing, and caching layers — with measurable before/after benchmarks.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <div class="service-icon">🛡️</div>
          <h3>AI Security Assessment</h3>
          <p>Prompt injection, data exfiltration risks, agent loop vulnerabilities, PII exposure, and model supply chain risks — reviewed against current threat models.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <div class="service-icon">🎓</div>
          <h3>Team Training &amp; Upskilling</h3>
          <p>Hands-on workshops tailored to your stack: prompt engineering, LLM APIs, RAG patterns, agent design, evaluation frameworks, and cost management culture.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <div class="service-icon">🗺️</div>
          <h3>AI Strategy &amp; Roadmap</h3>
          <p>Build-vs-buy decisions, vendor evaluation, capability sequencing, and a 6–12 month roadmap your engineering and product teams can actually execute.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How it Works -->
  <section class="consulting-how full-section">
    <div class="consulting-container">
      <h2>How the savings model works</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">
        Inspired by how cloud consultancies operate: I take a percentage of
        what I save you, so there's no risk for you to get started.
      </p>
      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-num">1</div>
          <h3>Intro Call</h3>
          <p>30 minutes to understand your stack, spend, and goals. I'll tell you honestly if I can help.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-num">2</div>
          <h3>Audit</h3>
          <p>2–4 week deep dive into your codebase, usage data, invoices, and architecture. No changes yet.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-num">3</div>
          <h3>Roadmap</h3>
          <p>Prioritized list of changes with projected savings per item. You decide what to implement.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-num">4</div>
          <h3>Implementation</h3>
          <p>I work alongside your team to ship the changes, with full documentation and handoff.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-num">5</div>
          <h3>Measure &amp; Share</h3>
          <p>30/60/90-day savings verified against baseline. You keep ~75%. I take ~25%.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section id="pricing" class="consulting-section full-section">
    <div class="consulting-container">
      <h2>Engagement options</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">
        Three ways to work together, depending on where you are and what you need.
      </p>

      <div class="pricing-grid">
        <!-- Intro Call -->
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <div class="pricing-tier">First step</div>
          <h3>Intro Call</h3>
          <p class="pricing-desc">
            A focused 30-minute conversation to diagnose your situation and
            decide if we're a fit — before any commitment.
          </p>
          <div class="price-main">$500</div>
          <div class="price-period">one-time / 30 minutes</div>
          <div class="price-qualifier">Credited toward any engagement</div>
          <hr class="pricing-divider" />
          <ul class="pricing-features">
            <li><span class="check">✓</span> Structured diagnostic session</li>
            <li><span class="check">✓</span> Written summary &amp; top 3 opportunities</li>
            <li><span class="check">✓</span> Honest assessment — I'll say if I can't help</li>
            <li><span class="check">✓</span> Secure payment via Stripe</li>
          </ul>
          <a href={STRIPE_INTRO_CALL_LINK} class="btn btn-outline pricing-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            Book via Stripe →
          </a>
          <p class="pricing-note">Instant confirmation. Schedule after payment.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Cost Savings Share — Featured -->
        <div class="pricing-card featured">
          <div class="pricing-badge">Most Popular</div>
          <div class="pricing-tier">Performance-based</div>
          <h3>Cost Savings Partnership</h3>
          <p class="pricing-desc">
            I audit your stack, implement optimizations, and take 25% of
            the annual savings I deliver. Zero upfront. Pure alignment.
          </p>
          <div class="price-main">25%</div>
          <div class="price-period">of documented annual savings</div>
          <div class="price-qualifier">Prorated monthly over 12 months</div>
          <hr class="pricing-divider" />
          <ul class="pricing-features">
            <li><span class="check">✓</span> Full audit (2–4 weeks)</li>
            <li><span class="check">✓</span> Prioritized savings roadmap</li>
            <li><span class="check">✓</span> Hands-on implementation support</li>
            <li><span class="check">✓</span> 90-day savings verification</li>
            <li><span class="check">✓</span> Monthly check-ins for 12 months</li>
            <li><span class="check">✓</span> No savings = no fee</li>
          </ul>
          <a href={CALENDLY_LINK} class="btn btn-primary pricing-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            Schedule Discovery Call →
          </a>
          <p class="pricing-note">Minimum qualifying spend: $50K/month on AI infrastructure</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Retainer -->
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <div class="pricing-tier">Ongoing advisory</div>
          <h3>Monthly Retainer</h3>
          <p class="pricing-desc">
            Dedicated hours each month for teams that need consistent
            strategic guidance, architecture review, and rapid-response support.
          </p>
          <div class="price-main">$15K</div>
          <div class="price-period">per month</div>
          <div class="price-qualifier">20 hours included · additional at $750/hr</div>
          <hr class="pricing-divider" />
          <ul class="pricing-features">
            <li><span class="check">✓</span> 20 hrs/month (strategy + hands-on)</li>
            <li><span class="check">✓</span> Async Slack/email access</li>
            <li><span class="check">✓</span> Code &amp; architecture reviews</li>
            <li><span class="check">✓</span> Incident response support</li>
            <li><span class="check">✓</span> Monthly written briefing</li>
            <li><span class="check">✓</span> 3-month minimum engagement</li>
          </ul>
          <a href={STRIPE_RETAINER_LINK} class="btn btn-outline pricing-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            Start Retainer →
          </a>
          <p class="pricing-note">Billed monthly via Stripe. Cancel with 30 days notice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Qualifying box -->
      <div class="qualify-box">
        <div class="qualify-icon">⚡</div>
        <div>
          <h4>Who qualifies for the savings partnership?</h4>
          <p>
            Your organization must be spending at least <strong>$50,000/month</strong> on AI
            infrastructure (tokens, embeddings, hosting, inference) to have enough surface area
            for a meaningful optimization engagement. Companies spending $100K+/month typically
            see the strongest returns. If you're below that threshold, the intro call or retainer
            are better starting points.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Savings math explainer -->
      <div class="savings-explainer">
        <h3>What does 25% of savings actually look like?</h3>
        <p class="savings-sub">
          Here's a real-world scenario based on typical outcomes. Your numbers will vary —
          this is why we audit first.
        </p>
        <div class="savings-math">
          <div class="savings-cell">
            <div class="cell-label">Your current spend</div>
            <div class="cell-value">$120K</div>
            <div class="cell-note">per month</div>
          </div>
          <div class="savings-cell">
            <div class="cell-label">Post-optimization</div>
            <div class="cell-value green">$48K</div>
            <div class="cell-note">per month (–60%)</div>
          </div>
          <div class="savings-cell">
            <div class="cell-label">Annual savings</div>
            <div class="cell-value green">$864K</div>
            <div class="cell-note">you keep 75%: <strong>$648K</strong></div>
          </div>
          <div class="savings-cell">
            <div class="cell-label">My share (25%)</div>
            <div class="cell-value cyan">$216K</div>
            <div class="cell-note">paid monthly: ~$18K/mo</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="savings-fine-print">
          Savings are calculated against a verified 90-day baseline established at engagement start.
          Methodology is agreed upon before any work begins. Payments are prorated monthly over 12
          months based on projected annual savings, with a true-up at the 6-month mark. You always
          retain the right to audit the calculations. Savings include direct token costs, compute,
          and any vendor fee reductions I negotiate on your behalf.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- About -->
  <section id="about" class="consulting-about full-section">
    <div class="consulting-container">
      <div class="about-inner">
        <div class="about-avatar">DL</div>
        <div class="about-content">
          <h2>Hi, I'm Dan Levy</h2>
          <p>
            I'm a software engineer and architect who has spent the last several years
            embedded in AI infrastructure — building, scaling, and auditing LLM-powered
            systems across fintech, developer tooling, and enterprise SaaS.
          </p>
          <p>
            I've seen what happens when AI costs get out of control, and I've built
            the frameworks to fix it. I write about AI architecture and engineering
            at <a href="/">danlevy.net</a> and
            work directly with a small number of companies each year.
          </p>
          <p>
            I'm not a large consultancy. You get me — reviewing your code, talking
            to your engineers, and doing the work. That's a feature, not a limitation.
          </p>
          <div class="about-tags">
            <span class="tag">LLM Architecture</span>
            <span class="tag">Token Optimization</span>
            <span class="tag">RAG Systems</span>
            <span class="tag">Prompt Engineering</span>
            <span class="tag">AI Security</span>
            <span class="tag">Cost Analysis</span>
            <span class="tag">OpenAI / Anthropic / Google</span>
            <span class="tag">Team Training</span>
            <span class="tag">TypeScript / Python</span>
            <span class="tag">Agent Design</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Banner -->
  <section class="consulting-cta full-section">
    <div class="consulting-container cta-inner">
      <h2>Not sure if you qualify?<br />Book the intro call.</h2>
      <p>
        30 minutes. $500. You'll leave with a clear picture of what's
        possible — or an honest answer that I'm not the right fit.
        Either way, you win.
      </p>
      <a href={STRIPE_INTRO_CALL_LINK} class="btn btn-primary btn-xl" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        Book Intro Call — $500 via Stripe →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  /* ── Full-width section override ── */
  .full-section {
    grid-column: full-width;
    width: 100%;
  }

  /* ── Container ── */
  .consulting-container {
    max-width: min(1120px, 100% - 3rem);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  /* ── Shared typography ── */
  h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.6rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.15;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .section-lead {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
    max-width: 560px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .gradient-text {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, hsl(180 100% 60%), hsl(322 100% 72%));
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  /* ── Buttons ── */
  .btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.18s;
    border: none;
    white-space: nowrap;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .btn-xl {
    padding: 1rem 2rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    border-radius: 1rem;
  }
  .btn-primary {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, hsl(180 100% 40%), hsl(322 100% 50%));
    color: #fff;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0, 210, 210, 0.25);
  }
  .btn-primary:hover {
    opacity: 0.9;
    transform: translateY(-1px);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 210, 210, 0.35);
  }
  .btn-outline {
    background: transparent;
    color: hsl(180 100% 65%);
    border: 2px solid hsl(180 100% 40%);
  }
  .btn-outline:hover {
    background: hsl(180 100% 40% / 0.15);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }
  .btn-ghost {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    color: #fff;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
    backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
  }
  .btn-ghost:hover {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.14);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }

  /* ── Hero ── */
  .consulting-hero {
    padding: 5rem 0 6rem;
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse at 70% 0%, hsl(180 100% 15% / 0.4) 0%, transparent 60%),
                radial-gradient(ellipse at 20% 80%, hsl(322 100% 20% / 0.3) 0%, transparent 60%),
                linear-gradient(180deg, #0d1117 0%, #0a0f16 100%);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.07);
  }

  .hero-badge {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
    border-radius: 100px;
    padding: 6px 16px 6px 10px;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: hsl(180 100% 70%);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .hero-badge-dot {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: hsl(120 100% 50%);
    animation: pulse 2s infinite;
  }

  @keyframes pulse {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1); }
    50% { opacity: 0.6; transform: scale(1.3); }
  }

  .consulting-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.8rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    line-height: 1.08;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .hero-sub {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.2rem);
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
    max-width: 580px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }

  .hero-stats {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    padding-top: 3rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
  }

  .stat-number {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    color: #fff;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .stat-number span {
    color: hsl(180 100% 60%);
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }

  /* ── Problem ── */
  .consulting-problem {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    background: #050b14;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
  }

  .consulting-problem h2 {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .problem-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: 1px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
    border-radius: 1.25rem;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .problem-item {
    background: #0a1120;
    padding: 2rem;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }

  .problem-item:hover {
    background: #0d1829;
  }

  .problem-icon {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .problem-item h3 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
  }

  .problem-item p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Services ── */
  .consulting-section {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    background: #0d1117;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
  }

  .services-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .service-card {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    border-radius: 1.25rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .service-card:hover {
    border-color: hsl(180 100% 40% / 0.4);
    background: rgba(0, 210, 210, 0.04);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .service-icon {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .service-card p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── How it Works ── */
  .consulting-how {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    background: #060d18;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
  }

  .steps {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr));
    gap: 0;
    position: relative;
  }

  .steps::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 2rem;
    left: 10%;
    right: 10%;
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, hsl(180 100% 40%), hsl(322 100% 50%));
    opacity: 0.2;
  }

  .step {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .step-num {
    width: 4rem;
    height: 4rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #0d1829;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 800;
